<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Nugs Downloader</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/public/assets/css/bulma.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"  href="/public/assets/css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <section class="section">
        <h1 class="title">Step One</h1>
        <h2 class="subtitle">Drag the buttons below into your bookmarks bar</h2>
        <div class="columns is-centered">
            <div class="column is-3">
                <div class="columns is-centered">
                    <div class="column">
                        <a id="nugs-bookmarklet" type="button" class="button is-primary" href="#">Nugs Downloader</a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="column">
                        <a id="livephish-bookmarklet" type="button" class="button is-primary" href="#">Live Phish Downloader</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h1 class="title">Step Two</h1>
        <h2 class="subtitle">
            In your browser, visit either <a href="https://play.nugs.net/">play.nugs.net</a> or <a href="https://plus.livephish.com/">plus.livephish.com</a> and navigate to a show.
        </h2>
        <p>The downloader will only work if inside a show (recording). The app does not allow for downloading single tracks.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h1 class="title">Step Three</h1>
        <h2 class="subtitle">
            Once you have found a ðŸ”¥ show, click the bookmarklet link (the bookmark you just added in your browser's bookmark bar)<br> that relates to the streaming platform you're currently on.
            (i.e. if you're on nugs.net, click the Nugs Downloader bookmarklet)
        </h2>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h1 class="title">Step Four</h1>
        <h2 class="subtitle">
            The server will start downloading your show!
        </h2>
        <p>Note, you can view the download status inside the terminal session where you originally ran <span class="is-family-monospace">npm run serve</span></p>
    </section>
</div>
<input id="server-url" type="hidden" value="<%=serverUrl%>">
<script src="assets/js/scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
